                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d657">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.48/521</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EAI1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Elkus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-18T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 18, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3280. Your 2387, January 8. Red Cross and Committee for Syrian Relief state that
                        <persName corresp="#p_DP2">Djemal Pasha</persName>’s request would largely
                    divert relief supplies from original purposes for which funds were solicited. If
                    possible have all supplies landed and distributed at Beirut. Only if absolutely
                    necessary concession may be made to have one-fourth landed at Jaffa, on
                    condition that <persName>Philip</persName>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d657fn3">
                        <persName>Hoffman Philip</persName>, Counselor of the Embassy at
                        Constantinople.</note> and Red Cross representatives from Beirut proceed to
                    Jaffa and supervise distribution there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
